üåê Core Concept (Simplified & Clean)
‚Ä¢	**Clean Season Model**: id, start_date, half_date, end_date (no name, no is_active - Apple simple)
‚Ä¢	**Date-Based Current Season**: Current season = where today's date falls between start/end dates
‚Ä¢	**Overlap Prevention**: Database constraint prevents overlapping seasons
‚Ä¢	**Computed Display Names**: Function-based, never out of sync, auto-generates "2025", "2025/26", "Spring '75"
‚Ä¢	**Helper Functions**: get_current_season(), get_season_by_date() - single source of truth
‚Ä¢	**No Over-Engineering**: No groups, timezones, backwards compatibility, or enterprise complexity
‚Ä¢	**UX Continuity**: Existing users see identical interface ("2025", "2024", "2023")
‚Ä¢	**Season Gap Protection**: Matches blocked when no active season (forces quick season creation)
‚Ä¢	**Quick Season Creation**: 15-second process - just start/end dates, that's it
‚Ä¢	**Decoupled Billing**: Season creation separate from billing setup (billing comes later)
‚Ä¢	**Direct Migration**: No backwards compatibility needed - you control everything
‚Ä¢	New Season defaults:
o	If previous season exists ‚Üí default start = previous end + 1 day, same length  
o	If no previous season ‚Üí default = current year (Jan‚ÄìDec)
o	Half-date auto-set = midpoint between start & end
o	Display name computed from date range
________________________________________
üìä Stats Model
‚Ä¢	Worker aggregates stats into 3 ranges:
o	start_date ‚Üí half_date (first half).
o	half_date ‚Üí end_date (second half).
o	start_date ‚Üí end_date (full season).
‚Ä¢	Legacy compatibility: existing ‚ÄúFull Season‚Äù and ‚ÄúHalf Season‚Äù views keep working ‚Äî now powered by Season lookups instead of hardcoded dates.
________________________________________
üí∞ Billing Model (planned for later)
At Season setup, organiser can choose:
‚Ä¢	Per-match fees (default per game, override per match).
‚Ä¢	Season fees with tiers (e.g. Gold ¬£100, Silver ¬£60, Casual = per-game).
‚Ä¢	Both (hybrid: some players on subs, others per-game).
Schema elements:
‚Ä¢	SeasonBilling ‚Üí stores billing mode.
‚Ä¢	SeasonTiers ‚Üí defines tiers (name, fee, type, optional caps).
‚Ä¢	SeasonMemberships ‚Üí links players to Season/tier (null = casual).
‚Ä¢	Games.override_fee ‚Üí allows per-match pricing.
________________________________________
üßë‚Äçü§ù‚Äçüßë Player Membership & Tiers
‚Ä¢	At Season start: organiser sees list of players with tickboxes for tiers.
‚Ä¢	Tiers are A or B and can have different prices
‚Ä¢	Unticked = casual (per-match).
‚Ä¢	Mid-season joins:
o	Default = casual.
o	Organiser can promote into a tier any time.
o	MVP billing = full season fee on promotion (no proration).
________________________________________
üîÑ Season Lifecycle & Rollover
‚Ä¢	At Season end:
o	Games still schedulable.
o	Stats + billing won‚Äôt show until new Season is created.
o	Prompt organiser: ‚ÄúCreate new season?‚Äù (pre-filled with defaults from last season).
‚Ä¢	Manual rollover first (safe).
‚Ä¢	Later: optional auto-rollover for recurring cycles.
‚Ä¢	Billing grace period: games can continue, but payments/stats wait until Season exists.
________________________________________
